&lt;p&gt;Inherited cardiac conditions Clinical Nurse specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a band 7 nurse to join the&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inherited Cardiac conditions (ICC) team at Barts Heart centre. The successful candidate will have 2 years’ experience as working as a band 6 within cardiac services and specific experience within ICC would be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to provide evidence of excellent teamwork skills and an ability to coordinate the assessment process within the multidisciplinary team. They will demonstrate strong communication skills and how these will be used within the MDT as well as with patients and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service is expanding and the successful candidate will contribute to service development and support positive changes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be committed to education for patients and also the clinical areas within the centre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Linda Moss lmoss2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fiona Kearl fiona.kearl@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joana Barbosa j.barbosa@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
